<subSubSection pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="52.[150,1437,151,1941]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,188,213]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male. Idiosoma elongated-oval (dorsal shield L/W ratio 1.3–1.4); frontal plates similar in dimensions to shoulder plates (shoulder/frontal plate L ratio 0.99–1.04); gnathosomal bay deep, narrow U-shaped (L/W ratio 4.6); medial margin of Cx-II/III relatively short; genital field elongated (L/W ratio 1.3–1.4); ejaculatory complex with large proximal chamber, proximal and distal arms short; excretory pore anterior to Vgl–2 and away from the line of primary sclerotization; ventral setae on P-4 short.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="52.[150,1437,151,1941]" box="[151,289,367,392]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,289,367,392]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="52.[150,1437,151,1941]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
Male. 
<emphasis box="[275,467,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">General features</emphasis>
—Idiosoma elongated-oval; frontal plates similar in dimensions to shoulder plates; frontal margin medially pointed, between anterolaterally pointed apodemes (
<figureCitation box="[1072,1184,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[154,1432,201,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-73@35.[151,1436,193,1918]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 25A–G. Monatractides epiales n. sp., holotype male, Kipungit River: A = frontal margin of idiosoma, dorsal view; B = dorsal shield; C = idiosoma, ventral view; D = palp, medial view; E = palp, lateral view; F = gnathosoma; G = I-L-5 and -6. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4927965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4927965/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 25A</figureCitation>
); Cxgl–4 located far anteriorly, near tips of Cx-I; gnathosomal bay deep, narrow U-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[993,1100,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[154,1432,201,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-73@35.[151,1436,193,1918]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 25A–G. Monatractides epiales n. sp., holotype male, Kipungit River: A = frontal margin of idiosoma, dorsal view; B = dorsal shield; C = idiosoma, ventral view; D = palp, medial view; E = palp, lateral view; F = gnathosoma; G = I-L-5 and -6. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4927965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4927965/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 25C</figureCitation>
); medial margin of Cx-II/III relatively short; genital field subrectangular in shape; ejaculatory complex characteristic (
<figureCitation box="[1209,1329,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1167,1189]" captionTargetBox="[257,1327,205,1136]" captionTargetId="figure-341@36.[236,1350,193,1145]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 26A–B. Ejaculatory complex. A = Monatractides epiales n. sp., Kipungit River. B = M. cf. macroporus (K. Viets, 1935), unnamed stream Bansadon Trail. Scale bar = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4927967" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4927967/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Figs. 26A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1345,1423,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1662,1684]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1641]" captionTargetId="figure-210@42.[151,1436,193,1641]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 30A–M. Photographs of ejaculatory complex. A Monatractides longiventris (K. Viets, 1939), Mahua stream. B M. oxystomus (K. Viets, 1935), Kipungit River. C–D M. cf. macroporus (K. Viets, 1935): C = stream Bansadon Trail; D = Little Lumotok stream. E–F M. epiales n. sp., Kipungit River: E = holotype; F = paratype. G M. phantasos n. sp., Great Lumotok stream. H M. phobetor n. sp., Little Lumotok stream. I–L M. morpheus n. sp. I = holotype, small stream Layang Layang; K = Kemantis stream; K = Little Lumotok stream. M M. heracles n. sp., Little Lumotok stream." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4927975" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4927975/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">30E–F</figureCitation>
), proximal chamber large, proximal and distal arms short, 
<emphasis box="[828,1005,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">carina anterior</emphasis>
short; suture line of Cx-IV distinct, originating from lateral edge of genital field and extending posteriorly beyond posterior margin of genital field; excretory pore and Vgl–2 away from the line of primary sclerotization, Vgl–2 slightly posterior to excretory pore; gnathosoma elongated in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[611,716,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[154,1432,201,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-73@35.[151,1436,193,1918]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 25A–G. Monatractides epiales n. sp., holotype male, Kipungit River: A = frontal margin of idiosoma, dorsal view; B = dorsal shield; C = idiosoma, ventral view; D = palp, medial view; E = palp, lateral view; F = gnathosoma; G = I-L-5 and -6. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4927965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4927965/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Fig. 25F</figureCitation>
), rostrum truncated; ventral and dorsal setae of P-2 and P-3 relatively strong and long, P-2 and P-3 distal margins without pointed tips, P-4 ventral setae short (
<figureCitation box="[1259,1405,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[154,1432,201,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-73@35.[151,1436,193,1918]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 25A–G. Monatractides epiales n. sp., holotype male, Kipungit River: A = frontal margin of idiosoma, dorsal view; B = dorsal shield; C = idiosoma, ventral view; D = palp, medial view; E = palp, lateral view; F = gnathosoma; G = I-L-5 and -6. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4927965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4927965/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Figs. 25D–E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="52.[150,1437,151,1941]" box="[151,313,729,752]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis box="[151,313,729,752]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Measurements</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="52.[150,1437,151,1941]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
Male (
<typeStatus box="[271,374,764,789]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">holotype</typeStatus>
; in parentheses 
<typeStatus box="[551,650,764,788]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">paratype</typeStatus>
, n = 1)—Idiosoma (ventral view: 
<figureCitation box="[1028,1140,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="35.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[154,1432,201,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-73@35.[151,1436,193,1918]" captionTargetPageId="35" captionText="FIGURE 25A–G. Monatractides epiales n. sp., holotype male, Kipungit River: A = frontal margin of idiosoma, dorsal view; B = dorsal shield; C = idiosoma, ventral view; D = palp, medial view; E = palp, lateral view; F = gnathosoma; G = I-L-5 and -6. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4927965" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4927965/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Figs. 25C</figureCitation>
, 
