<subSubSection pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="52.[150,1437,151,1941]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1519,1544]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after Epiales (Ancient Greek: Ἐπιάλης), who was a spirit of nightmares. The species name is a noun in apposition (in the nominative case), despite the Recommendation 31A of the ICZN (1999) about avoidance of personal names as nouns in appositions, because there is no case for it being confusing or misleading.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="52.[150,1437,151,1941]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,1663,1688]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Discussion</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Pešić &amp; Smit, 2014" authorityName="Pešić &amp; Smit" authorityYear="2014" box="[345,600,1663,1688]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="epiales" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[345,600,1663,1688]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Monatractides epiales</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[613,683,1663,1688]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[613,675,1663,1688]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">n. sp</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is rather similar and probably represent a sister species of 
<taxonomicName authority="(K. Viets, 1935)" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="K. Viets" baseAuthorityYear="1935" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macroporus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">M. macroporus</emphasis>
(K. 
<bibRefCitation author="Viets, K." box="[335,464,1700,1725]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="1 - 113" refId="ref38385" refString="Viets, K. (1935) Die Wassermilben von Sumatra, Java und Bali nach den Ergebnissen der Deutschen Limnologischen Sunda- Expedition. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, Supplement 14 (Tropische Binnengewasser), 1 - 113." type="journal article" year="1935">Viets, 1935</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(see above) with respect to the general shape of idiosoma and palps. Main differences between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="K. Viets" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[254,429,1737,1760]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macroporus">
<emphasis box="[254,429,1737,1760]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">M. macroporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Pešić &amp; Smit, 2014" authorityName="Pešić &amp; Smit" authorityYear="2014" box="[490,610,1735,1760]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="epiales" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[490,610,1735,1760]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">M. epiales</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[620,687,1735,1760]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[620,679,1735,1760]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">n. sp</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
are found in the morphology of ejaculatory complex (normallydeveloped with small proximal chamber in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="K. Viets" baseAuthorityYear="1935" box="[646,819,1773,1796]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macroporus">
<emphasis box="[646,819,1773,1796]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">M. macroporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. proximal chamber large, proximal and distal arms short, 
<emphasis box="[220,393,1808,1831]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">carina anterior</emphasis>
short in 
<taxonomicName authority="Pešić &amp; Smit, 2014" authorityName="Pešić &amp; Smit" authorityYear="2014" box="[491,607,1807,1832]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="epiales" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[491,607,1807,1832]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">M. epiales</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[614,674,1807,1832]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[614,670,1807,1832]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">n. sp</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
—compare 
<figureCitation box="[808,1003,1807,1832]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="36.[151,250,1167,1189]" captionTargetBox="[257,1327,205,1136]" captionTargetId="figure-341@36.[236,1350,193,1145]" captionTargetPageId="36" captionText="FIGURE 26A–B. Ejaculatory complex. A = Monatractides epiales n. sp., Kipungit River. B = M. cf. macroporus (K. Viets, 1935), unnamed stream Bansadon Trail. Scale bar = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4927967" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4927967/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Figs. 26A and -B</figureCitation>
). The female assigned to 
<taxonomicName authority="Pešić &amp; Smit, 2014" authorityName="Pešić &amp; Smit" authorityYear="2014" box="[1290,1406,1807,1832]" class="Arachnida" family="Torrenticolidae" genus="Monatractides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="epiales" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1290,1406,1807,1832]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">M. epiales</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="52" pageNumber="53" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">n. sp</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be identified on the basis of a relatively larger extension of the genital field (L ratio genital/idiosoma 0.21).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="52.[150,1437,151,1941]" box="[199,812,1879,1904]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,1879,1904]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Habitat.</emphasis>
Sandy/bouldery stream, shaded by rain forest
</paragraph>
